    1   /* File    : rt_matrx.c
    2    * Abstract:
    3    *      Implements stand alone matrix access and creation routines.
    4    *	There are two types of MATLAB objects which can be "passed" to
    5    *	the generated code, a 2D real matrix and a string. Strings are
    6    *	passed as 2D real matrices. The first two elements of an S-function
    7    *	parameters are the row and column (m and n) dimensions respectively.
    8    *	These are followed by the matrix data.
    9    */

  212   /* Function: mxCreateCharMatrixFromStrings ====================================
  213    * Abstract:
  214    *	Create a string array initialized to the strings in str.
  215    */
  216   
  217   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  218   #ifdef __cplusplus
  219   extern "C" {
  220   #endif
  221   END_PUBLIC
  222   
  223   PUBLIC mxArray *rt_mxCreateCharMatrixFromStrings(int_T m, const char_T **str)
  224   {
  225       int_T nchars;
  226       int_T i, n;
  227       mxArray *pa;
  228   
  229       n = 0;
  230       for (i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
  231   	nchars = (int_T)strlen(str[i]);
  232   	if (nchars > n) {
  233   	    n = nchars;
  234   	}
  235       }
  236       /*LINTED E_PASS_INT_TO_SMALL_INT*/
  237       pa = (mxArray *)malloc((m*n+2)*sizeof(real_T));
  238       if(pa!=NULL) {
  239   	mxChar *chars;
  240   	int_T  j;
  241   	_mxSetM(pa, m);
  242   	_mxSetN(pa, n);
  243   	chars = mxGetPr(pa);
  244   	for (j = 0; j < m; ++j) {
  245   	    const char_T *src  = str[j];
  246   	    mxChar *dest = chars + j;
  247   
  248   	    nchars = (int_T)strlen(src);
  249   	    i = nchars;
  250   	    while (i--) {
  251   		*dest = *src++;
  252   		 dest += m;
  253   	    }
  254   	    i = n - nchars;
  255   	    while (i--) {
  256   		*dest = 0.0;
  257   		dest += m;
  258   	    }
  259   	}
  260       }
  261       return pa;
  262   } /* end mxCreateCharMatrixFromStrings */
  263   
  264   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  265   #ifdef __cplusplus
  266   }
  267   #endif
  268   END_PUBLIC

  270   /* Function: mxCreateString ===================================================
  271    * Abstract:
  272    *	Create a 1-by-n string array initialized to null terminated string
  273    *	where n is the length of the string.
  274    */
  275   
  276   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  277   #ifdef __cplusplus
  278   extern "C" {
  279   #endif
  280   END_PUBLIC
  281   
  282   PUBLIC mxArray *rt_mxCreateString(const char *str)
  283   {
  284       int_T   len = (int_T)strlen(str);
  285       /*LINTED E_PASS_INT_TO_SMALL_INT*/
  286       mxArray *pa = (mxArray *)malloc((len+2)*sizeof(real_T));
  287   
  288       if(pa!=NULL) {
  289   	real_T *pr;
  290   	const unsigned char *ustr_ptr = (const unsigned char *) str;
  291   
  292   	_mxSetM(pa, 1);
  293   	_mxSetN(pa, len);
  294   	pr = mxGetPr(pa);
  295   	while (len--) {
  296               *pr++ = (real_T)*ustr_ptr++;
  297           }
  298       }
  299       return(pa);
  300   
  301   } /* end mxCreateString */
  302   
  303   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  304   #ifdef __cplusplus
  305   }
  306   #endif
  307   END_PUBLIC

  309   /* Function: mxCreateDoubleMatrix =============================================
  310    * Abstract:
  311    *	Create a two-dimensional array to hold real_T data,
  312    *	initialize each data element to 0.
  313    */
  314   /*LINTLIBRARY*/
  315   
  316   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  317   #ifdef __cplusplus
  318   extern "C" {
  319   #endif
  320   END_PUBLIC
  321   
  322   PUBLIC mxArray *rt_mxCreateDoubleMatrix(int m, int n, mxComplexity flag)
  323   {
  324       if (flag == mxREAL) {
  325           mxArray *pa = (mxArray *)calloc(m*n+2, sizeof(real_T));
  326           if(pa!=NULL) {
  327               _mxSetM(pa, m);
  328               _mxSetN(pa, n);
  329           }
  330           return(pa);
  331       } else {
  332           return(NULL);
  333       }
  334   
  335   } /* end mxCreateDoubleMatrix */
  336   
  337   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  338   #ifdef __cplusplus
  339   }
  340   #endif
  341   END_PUBLIC

  344    * Abstract:
  345    *	Create a numeric array and initialize all its data elements to 0.
  346    */
  347   
  348   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  349   #ifdef __cplusplus
  350   extern "C" {

  352   END_PUBLIC
  353   
  354   PUBLIC mxArray *rt_mxCreateNumericArray(int_T ndims, const int_T *dims, 
  355                                           mxClassID classid, mxComplexity flag)
  356   {
  357       if (ndims == 2 && classid==mxDOUBLE_CLASS) {
  358           return(rt_mxCreateDoubleMatrix(dims[0], dims[1], flag));
  359       } else {
  360           return(NULL);
  361       }
  362   
  363   } /* end mxCreateNumericArray */

  366   #ifdef __cplusplus
  367   }

  371   /* Function: mxDuplicateArray =================================================
  372    * Abstract:
  373    *	Make a deep copy of an array, return a pointer to the copy.
  374    */
  375   
  376   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  377   #ifdef __cplusplus
  378   extern "C" {
  379   #endif
  380   END_PUBLIC
  381   
  382   PUBLIC mxArray *rt_mxDuplicateArray(const mxArray *pa)
  383   {
  384       /*LINTED E_ASSIGN_INT_TO_SMALL_INT*/
  385       size_t   nbytes = (mxGetNumberOfElements(pa)+2)*mxGetElementSize(pa);
  386       mxArray *pcopy = (mxArray *)malloc(nbytes);
  387   
  388       if (pcopy!=NULL) {
  389   	(void)memcpy(pcopy, pa, nbytes);
  390       }
  391       return(pcopy);
  392   
  393   } /* end mxDuplicateArray */
  394   
  395   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  396   #ifdef __cplusplus
  397   }
  398   #endif
  399   END_PUBLIC

  402    * Abstract:

  406

  427   /* Function: mxGetEps =========================================================
  428    * Abstract:
  429    *	Return eps, the difference between 1.0 and the least value
  430    *	greater than 1.0 that is representable as a real_T.
  431    *	NOTE: Assumes real_T is either double or float.
  432    */
  433   
  434   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  435   #ifdef __cplusplus
  436   extern "C" {
  437   #endif
  438   END_PUBLIC
  439   
  440   PUBLIC real_T rt_mxGetEps(void)
  441   {
  442       return (sizeof(double)==sizeof(real_T)) ? DBL_EPSILON : FLT_EPSILON;
  443   }
  444   
  445   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  446   #ifdef __cplusplus
  447   }
  448   #endif

  451   /* Function: mxGetString ======================================================
  452    * Abstract:
  453    *	Converts a string array to a C-style string.
  454    */
  455   
  456   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  457   #ifdef __cplusplus
  458   extern "C" {
  459   #endif
  460   END_PUBLIC
  461   
  462   PUBLIC int_T rt_mxGetString(const mxArray *pa, char_T *buf, int_T buflen)
  463   {
  464       int_T        nchars;
  465       const real_T *pr;
  466       char_T       *pc;
  467       int_T        truncate = 0;
  468   
  469       nchars = (int_T)mxGetNumberOfElements(pa);
  470       if (nchars >= buflen) {
  471   	/* leave room for null byte */
  472   	nchars = buflen - 1;
  473   	truncate = 1;
  474       }
  475       pc = buf;
  476       pr = mxGetPr(pa);
  477       while (nchars--) {
  478   	*pc++ = (char) (*pr++ + .5);
  479       }
  480       *pc = '\0';
  481       return truncate;
  482   } /* end mxGetString */
  483   
  484   BEGIN_PUBLIC
  485   #ifdef __cplusplus
  486   }
  487   #endif
  488   END_PUBLIC
